blocks.name: etransclem38
blocks.content: ` P ` divides the I -th derivative of ` F ` applied to ` J ` . if it is not the case that ` I = P - 1 ` and ` J = 0 ` . This is case 1 and the second part of case 2 proven in in [Juillerat] p. 13 . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 5-Apr-2020.)

blocks.content: This is the proof for equation *(7) in [Juillerat] p. 12. The proven equality will lead to a contradiction, because the left-hand side goes to ` 0 ` for large ` P ` , but the right-hand side is a nonzero integer. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 5-Apr-2020.)

blocks.content: ` _e ` is transcendental. Section *5 of [Juillerat] p. 11 can be used as a reference for this proof. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 5-Apr-2020.)
